      "content": "I hear the absolute exhaustion in your words, and it is completely understandable to feel that the usual coping mechanisms aren't enough when your entire future seems erased at once. Even though the weight feels permanent, it is crucial to recognize that this state of being is a symptom of profound grief, not an accurate reflection of your actual capacity to ever recover or build again. Please consider speaking with a crisis counselor right now, not just to talk about the feeling of hopelessness, but to get immediate, stable support for the pain that is currently crushing you.",
